Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1} into strips. Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Quarter @lime{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine scallion whites, juice from half the lime, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Stir until sugar and salt have mostly dissolved. Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and ginger; season with salt and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat. Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer beef to a #plate{} and set aside. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in pan used for beef over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and onion; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Return beef to pan and add @teriyaki sauce{8%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, until mixture is coated and sauce is slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}. In a second small bowl, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @ponzu sauce{6%milliliters}, and @sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste.

Divide beef filling and pickled scallion whites between tortillas. Drizzle with sriracha-ponzu mayo and top with scallion greens. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Everything tastes better in taco form. These marvelous tacos with teriyaki beef and sriracha-ponzu mayo are ready in just 25 minutes!